description: From the Latin superannuatus (“more than one year old”), from super (“over”) (English super-) + annus (“year”) (English annual).

adjectives.description: superannuated (comparative more superannuated, superlative most superannuated)

examples: Synonyms: archaic, dated, out of date, outdated, outmoded; see also Thesaurus:obsolete

entries.meaning: Retired or discarded due to age.
examples: Synonyms: decrepit, long in the tooth, over the hill; see also Thesaurus:elderly

entries.meaning: simple past tense and past participle of superannuate
